    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>An object is projected from the Earth's surface.  What is the least velocity (the escape velocity) of projection in order to escape the gravitational field, ignoring air resistance.</p>
<p>The equation of motion is \[m\, v{dv\over dx} = -m\, g{R^2\over x^2}\]</p>
<p>where the mass of the object is \(m\), its distance from the centre of the Earth is \(x\) and the radius of the Earth is \(R\).</p>
<p>\(u_{min} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p><p>If \( R = {@R_e@} \, \textrm{km}\) and \( g = {@g_val@} \, \textrm{m s}^{-2}\), what is the value of the escape velocity? Keep 1 d.p.</p><p>\( u_{min} = \)&nbsp;[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] \(\textrm{km s}^{-1}\) [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
